3. Bb5 { In this chapter, I'll explain some thematic strategic ideas in the Spanish or Ruy Lopez, followed by illustrating games for each pattern. Not all the games will feature the Wormald Attack, but these ideas can be present in our games, and they are worth learning to gain a better understanding of the opening. } *

[Event "The Vigorous Wormald Attack: A Practical White Repertoire vs. 1.e4 e5"]
[White "Typical Plans in the Spanish Opening"]
[Black "Knight b1-d2-f1-g3"]
[Date "2024.11.06"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/1N6 w - - 0 1"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/41625726"]

{ The knight transfer from the queenside to the g3-square is a very thematic strategic idea in many Ruy Lopez systems. It is a multi-purpose maneuver:

1 The knight can join the attack from the f5- or h5-squares.

2 The knight strengthens the defense of the e4-pawn.

3 The knight steps out of the way of White's queen and dark-squared bishop, allowing an easier development for White. } 1. -- {[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f1,Gf1g3]} *

