1. -- {[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f1,Gf1g3][%csl Gg4,Gh3]} { The knight transfer from the queenside to the g3-square with the pawns on h3 and g4 is a very thematic strategic idea in the Ruy Lopez.

This is a very principled maneuver that can be executed after castling or even with our king still on e1. White's basic idea after completing this maneuver is to launch a kingside attack, though the knight is also useful as a defender of the e4-pawn. } *

