[Black "The f4-break"]
[Date "2024.11.06"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "6k1/5p1p/3p2p1/3Pp3/4PPP1/7P/8/6K1 w - - 0 1"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/41625746"]

1. -- {[%csl Ge5]} { In many Ruy Lopez systems, one of the most typical plans once the center is closed is White's pawn break on f4.

Once we have executed the break, it's essential to prevent Black from landing a knight on the ideal e5-square. If that happens, we need to make sure we can quickly exchange it for one of our knights.

White's basic idea is to launch a quick kingside attack using the open f-file.

Of course, we need to keep our e-pawn perfectly protected because it becomes a severe weakness after we have pushed f4. } *

