1. e4 e5 
2. Nf3 Nc6 
3. Bb5 a6 
4. Ba4 Nf6 
5. Qe2 {[%mdl 32768]} { The Wormald Attack is a system where we postpone castling to wait and see what our opponent does first. Only when they commit their position will we decide whether to play d3 or d4 and whether to castle or go h3-g4 instead. The queen on e2 protects the pawn, and we save a tempo on Re1. Also, the queen steps out of the d-file, which is likely to be opened and is a much more suitable place for a white rook. } b5 { Black can play ...b5 now, or after ...Be7. Even playing it after ...d6 is possible. They are just transpositions. } 
6. Bb3 Be7 { This is one of Black's main options to fight the Wormald Attack, and will have its own chapter. [/course/259787/8] Black wants to play ...d6 and castle short. } ( { However, this is not as critical as } 6...Bc5 { , which we'll cover in another chapter. [/course/259787/9] } ) ( 6...Bb7 7.c3 Be7 { and now, if White doesn't want to transpose, } 8.d3 { is possible. } { 8.d4 d6 will end up transposing into other lines after both sides castle. } ) 
7. c3 { I like starting with this to enable Bc2 but also to toy with the d4 idea. Also, we may prepare h3 and g4 without castling. } d5 { This is an excellent gambit not worth accepting. } 
8. d3 ( { Accepting the gambit doesn't look sensible. } 8.exd5?! Nxd5 9.Nxe5 Nxe5 10.Qxe5 Nf6 { reminds me of the Marshall Gambit but in a worse version for White! Black enjoys quite superior development, and I don't know why our queen is standing on an open file. } ) O-O 
9. O-O Bb7 
10. Nbd2 Re8 
11. a3 {[%csl Gb3]} { Having a safe square on a2 for our bishop in case it's needed is always nice. } Na5 
12. Ba2 ( 12.Bc2 { is interesting, too, for sure. } ) c5 
13. b4 Nc6 
14. bxc5 ( { This was the right call. } 14.exd5 Nxd5 15.Ne4 { was played in the model game [/variation/41632193/#/14/b] Short-Huebner in an almost identical position. } ) Bxc5 
15. exd5 {[%cal Gd2e4]} { And now we vacate the e4-square for our knight. } Nxd5 
16. Ne4 Be7 
17. Nfg5 {[%cal Ge2h5,Ge2f3,Gf3d5,Ga2d5,Gg5f7][%csl Rd5,Rf7]} { With a powerful kingside attack. } *

