10. g4?! { My personal preference is having the knight on d2 before going for this, and only against ...d6 setups because then we have won a tempo. } Be6?! { Now that Black has wasted one tempo, I think the position is interesting for White. } ( 10...a5! { This strikes me as the best option. } 11.g5 dxe4 12.dxe4 { Now, g6 seems a powerful threat. } 12...a4 { With the idea of retreating the knight to h5 when this bishop is no longer pinning the f-pawn. Thus, Black stops g6 and is better. } ) 
